{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"Storing a PASS review summary is blocked when any stored dimension finding for the same round has a FAIL verdict.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Observed in this behavior: summary-write logic must read stored per-dimension findings for the same round and enforce a cross-record invariant (no PASS summary if any FAIL finding). Hypothetical elsewhere: real network/LLM failures in review agents. MOCK-MISS: yes, failure appears at module boundary (summary writer + findings store/query), not just one pure function. REAL-INFRA: no explicit OS/network/subprocess requirement. LLM-DEP: no, verdict check is deterministic on stored data. MULTI-STEP: no multi-agent pipeline required. Rejection gate: System/Agentic/Workflow are disqualified because behavior text only requires checking stored findings vs summary write, not real infrastructure or model output.","test_description":"Use an in-process persistence layer (e.g., test DB/repository). Seed one review round with at least one FAIL dimension finding, then attempt to persist a PASS summary for that same round. Assert the write is rejected (or transaction rolled back) and the stored state remains non-PASS.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.25,"Integration":0.68,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"Stop-gate verdict computation reads per-dimension stored findings directly and does not rely only on hand-written summary text.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Observed in this behavior: gate computation must pull persisted per-dimension findings and ignore contradictory manual summary text. Hypothetical elsewhere: transport errors or model-quality drift. MOCK-MISS: yes, bug is in wiring between gate logic and persistence source selection (summary text vs findings store). REAL-INFRA: no explicit need for real HTTP/OS/subprocess. LLM-DEP: no, correctness is deterministic from stored verdicts. MULTI-STEP: no. Rejection gate: higher levels are disqualified because behavior explicitly targets data-source choice inside gate computation.","test_description":"Seed storage with findings containing at least one FAIL, and separately store a hand-written summary claiming all PASS. Run stop-gate computation through normal service wiring. Assert gate verdict is non-PASS and is derived from stored findings, not summary text.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.2,"Integration":0.72,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"Manual summary text overrides require an explicit override flag and produce an auditable warning record.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Observed in this behavior: override acceptance must be gated by an explicit flag and must emit/store an audit warning record. Hypothetical elsewhere: centralized logging infra outages. MOCK-MISS: yes, failure occurs when validation, summary persistence, and audit-record writer interact. REAL-INFRA: no explicit requirement for real OS/network; in-process audit repository is sufficient to catch logic/wiring bugs. LLM-DEP: none. MULTI-STEP: none. Rejection gate: System/Agentic/Workflow disqualified because behavior text is about policy enforcement and audit recording, not external infra/model behavior.","test_description":"Attempt manual summary override without override flag and assert rejection. Then retry with override flag and assert success plus creation of an auditable warning record (includes round id, actor, reason, timestamp/event type) in the audit store.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.15,"Integration":0.75,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"After Phase 4 fixes, the review loop cannot finalize PASS unless a fresh review-agent round is executed on the updated diff.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Observed in this behavior: orchestrator must enforce freshness binding between updated diff and latest review round before final PASS. Hypothetical elsewhere: quality of LLM judgments inside the round. MOCK-MISS: yes, failure is at module boundaries among diff-tracking state, round metadata, and finalization gate. REAL-INFRA: behavior text does not require real subprocess/git/network; freshness can be validated via stored diff identifiers. LLM-DEP: not required for this behavior because it checks existence/freshness of a round, not model output quality. MULTI-STEP: sequence exists, but not multiple real agentic steps; deterministic state transitions suffice. Rejection gate: Agentic/Workflow were considered but disqualified by behavior wording focused on 'fresh round executed on updated diff' rather than correctness of generated review content.","test_description":"Simulate Phase 4 producing a new diff id/hash after fixes while latest review round references the old diff. Run finalization and assert PASS is blocked with reason requiring fresh review round. Add a new round tied to the new diff and assert finalization can proceed only then.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.08,"Integration":0.78,"System":0.04,"Agentic":0.06,"Workflow":0.04}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"If review rounds are exhausted with unresolved MUST-FIX findings, the flow emits an escalation outcome instead of PASS.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Observed in this behavior: end-of-loop controller must combine round-limit state with persisted MUST-FIX unresolved findings to choose escalation outcome. Hypothetical elsewhere: notification transport/network failures. MOCK-MISS: yes, failure is in coordination across round counter, findings repository, and outcome emitter. REAL-INFRA: no explicit need for OS/network/subprocess to detect this policy failure. LLM-DEP: none; uses stored severity/status. MULTI-STEP: no multi-agent requirement. Rejection gate: System/Agentic/Workflow disqualified because behavior is deterministic policy branching over local state.","test_description":"Configure max rounds reached and seed unresolved MUST-FIX findings. Execute termination step of review flow through real module wiring. Assert emitted outcome is escalation (with PASS explicitly false/absent) and that no PASS summary/final state is persisted.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.12,"Integration":0.8,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.02}}]}
